   "source": [
    "20.⁠ ⁠Write a program to reverse a string.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a5f6c2a4-b7a5-401e-820d-2b7bf014053a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "TO REVERSE THE STRING WE NEED A SLICINING METHOD WHICH IS EASY CAN BRING OUTPUT IN ONE LINE [::-1]\n",
    "[start:stop:step]\n",
    "   0     0   -1"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "9fe26059-ff68-4f1b-a74e-bbcb3f14e68b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "esreveR\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "a = \"Reverse\"\n",
    "b = a[::-1]\n",
    "print(b)"
   ]
  }
